[MBD] — Mel Bhoy Denaquel · Personal Portfolio
A handcrafted personal portfolio built with HTML, SCSS (Sass), and vanilla JavaScript. Designed to feel human — no templates, no frameworks, no generic AI aesthetic.

✨ Features
Dark / Light mode — system preference detected automatically, with a manual toggle

Boska + Satoshi typography pairing — distinctive display serif with a clean grotesque body font

Responsive layout — mobile-first, tested from 375px to 1440px

Smooth animations — scroll reveals, hover states, modal transitions

Hire Me modal — contact form overlay with backdrop blur

Project showcase — featured project + supporting cards grid

Availability badge — live "open to work" status indicator with pulse animation

Stack tags — interactive tech badges in the hero section

Accessible — semantic HTML, keyboard navigation, visible focus rings, ARIA labels

🗂 Project Structure
text
new_portfolio/
├── index.html              # Main HTML file
├── style.css               # Compiled CSS (do not edit directly)
├── main.js                 # Theme toggle, modal, scroll animations
├── assets/
│   └── photo.jpg           # Profile photo
└── scss/
    ├── main.sass           # Sass entry point (@import all partials)
    ├── _tokens.sass        # Design tokens — colors, spacing, type scale
    ├── _base.sass          # Reset, base styles, typography
    ├── _components.sass    # Navbar, buttons, hero, stack tags
    ├── _content.sass       # Projects, About, Contact sections
    └── _modal.sass         # Modal backdrop and animation
🚀 Getting Started
Prerequisites
Node.js (for Sass CLI)

Sass — install globally via npm:

bash
npm install -g sass
Live Server (VS Code extension recommended)

Run Locally
Clone or download the repository into your local machine.

Open the new_portfolio/ folder in VS Code.

Start the Sass watcher to compile SCSS to CSS on save:

bash
sass --watch scss/main.sass:style.css --silence-deprecation=import
Launch Live Server — right-click index.html → Open with Live Server, or click Go Live in the VS Code status bar.

Open your browser at http://127.0.0.1:5500/index.html.

Build for Production
Compile a minified CSS for deployment:

bash
sass scss/main.sass:style.css --style=compressed --silence-deprecation=import
🎨 Design System
Color Palette
Token	Light	Dark	Usage
--color-bg	#f7f6f2	#111110	Page background
--color-surface	#f9f8f5	#1a1917	Card / nav surfaces
--color-text	#1e1c18	#e8e6e1	Primary text
--color-text-muted	#6b6a65	#7c7b76	Secondary text
--color-primary	#01696f	#4f9ea3	Accent — teal
Typography
Role	Font	Sizes
Display / Headings	Boska (Fontshare)	--text-xl → --text-3xl
Body / UI	Satoshi (Fontshare)	--text-xs → --text-lg
Fluid Type Scale
All font sizes use clamp() — they scale smoothly between mobile and desktop:

text
--text-xs   → 12px – 14px
--text-sm   → 14px – 16px
--text-base → 16px – 18px
--text-lg   → 18px – 24px
--text-xl   → 24px – 36px
--text-2xl  → 32px – 56px
--text-3xl  → 40px – 80px
🛠 Tech Stack
Technology	Purpose
HTML5	Semantic structure
CSS3 / Custom Properties	Design tokens, layout, animations
Sass (SCSS indented syntax)	Modular styles, variables, mixins
Vanilla JavaScript	Theme toggle, modals, scroll reveals
Fontshare CDN	Boska + Satoshi fonts
Lucide Icons	Lightweight SVG icon set
📐 Sass Architecture
The SCSS follows a partial-based architecture — each file has a single responsibility:

_tokens.sass — all design tokens (colors, spacing, radius, transitions)

_base.sass — CSS reset and global element styles

_components.sass — navbar, buttons, hero section, stack tags, footer

_modal.sass — modal backdrop, open/close animations

_content.sass — projects grid, about section, contact section

All partials are imported in main.sass in the correct dependency order.

Note: The project uses Sass @import with the --silence-deprecation=import flag. Migrating to @use/@forward is planned for a future update.

📱 Responsive Breakpoints
Breakpoint	Behavior
> 900px	Full hero grid — text left, photo right
≤ 900px	Photo hidden, text full width
≤ 768px	Projects stack to single column
≤ 600px	Nav links hidden (mobile layout)
≤ 480px	Hire Me button hidden, CTA stacks vertically
⚙️ Customization
Update your info
All personal content is in index.html. Search for these sections to update:

Hero heading — <h1 class="hero-heading">

Bio / subtitle — <p class="hero-sub">

Stack tags — <span class="stack-tag"> list

Projects — .project-card blocks inside the Work modal

About text — .about-text paragraphs

Contact email — <a class="contact-email">

Social links — .contact-social anchor tags

Swap your photo
Replace assets/photo.jpg with your own photo. Keep the filename the same, or update the src in index.html:

xml
<img src="./assets/your-photo.jpg" class="hero-photo" alt="Your Name" ... />
Change accent color
In _tokens.sass, update the primary color variables:

less
$color-primary:       #01696f  // light mode accent
$color-primary-hover: #0c4e54  // light mode hover
Also update the dark mode overrides in the [data-theme="dark"] block in style.css or _tokens.sass.

🌐 Deployment
This is a static site — deploy to any static host:

GitHub Pages — push to a gh-pages branch or enable Pages on main

Netlify — drag and drop the new_portfolio/ folder

Vercel — connect the repo, set output directory to new_portfolio/

Make sure to run the production Sass build before deploying so style.css is up to date.

